<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I saw him interviewed the other week on <a href="http://www.charlierose.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Charlie Rose Show</a>, easily the best show on Television.
<br />

<br />
While he had always maintained in the past he would be finishing the series with #3 (in chronology), he wouldn't rule out doing a 7-9.  He did say he had plans to go back to more filmaking that was more on the lines of what originally interested him (THX-1138).  In other words, more innovative, less hollywood-stereotype films.  
<br />

<br />
Interestingly, when it was first screened, the studio balked at releasing American Graffiti.  For its time, the studio execs didn't think audiences would go for it given the multiple storylines.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
